unittitle_ssm: Independent Order of Odd Fellows Council 837 minute book
abstract_ssm: The Independent Order of Odd Fellows (IOOF) was an international fraternal organization founded in Baltimore, MD in 1819 and became the first fraternal organization open to both men and women in 1851.  This collection contains the handwritten minutes of meetings of the IOOF Council 837 of Brooklyn, N.Y. from 1855 (when it was founded) to 1856 compiled by Secretary Cornelius Stryker.
